    comments: "The low-budget feel gives makes it seem as if it is a play (which it is trying to do)"
  }
  production_design {
    rating: "Good"
    comments: "Very Wes Anderson with its use of cheap sets and color palletes (something I do enjoy about his movies)"
  }
  plot_structure: "Plot Structure was a mess as weaving between the top level narration with the play itself made it unnecessarily confusing with it leaving no room for the main story (the play) to actually develop"
  pacing: "Pacing was on the faster side as it tried to mimic that of a play (but it felt like there could have been 15-20 minutes of more plot to make the story more interesting)"
  climax: "Climax was incredibly boring as it did not really feel like anything happened"
  tone: "Tone was very Wes Anderson as it was quirky with mixes of non-sequitor humor"
  final_notes: ""
  overall: "Overall, a very Wes Anderson movie that misses the mark as his typical confusing storytelling and bland dialogue/acting outweighs his strengths in cinematography and produciton design as the movie just feels very boring and not memorable"
